title: Bioinformatics Models and Algorithms
description: Covers bioinformatics models and algorithms: the use of computational techniques to convert the masses of information from biochemical experiments (DNA sequencing, DNA chips, and other high-throughput experimental methods) into useful information. Emphasis is on DNA and protein sequence alignment and analysis.

pre_req_data.text: Enrollment is restricted to graduate students. Undergraduates may enroll with prerequisite(s): BME 160; and CSE 107 or STAT 131; and concurrent enrollment in BIOC 100A.
